SHADOW DANCER
=============
Practice Mode - Hold A, B, C and press START at the title screen.

Free 1 Ups - In the bonus round, do not hit any ninjas and you will get a
1-Up for doing nothing!


SONIC THE HEDGEHOG
==================
Stage Select - At the title screen, press UP, DOWN, LEFT, RIGHT and you will
hear a short ringing sound. Then, just hold button A and press START.

Debug Mode - At the title screen, enter the following code: Press and hold
each combination for a few seconds) UP and C, DOWN and C, LEFT and C, 
RIGHT and C. When you hear the chime, hold down the A button and press START.
Now when Sonic enters Level 1 he can do the following things:
   Press B and he will become a new character.
   Press A and he will change characters.
   Press C and that character will multiply.
   Then press B again to turn him back to Sonic.

Power Sneakers - At the beginning of Stage 1, Level 3, roll into a ball and 
hit the springboard. When you fly into the air, push to the left so that you
will land on the platform. There you will find a 1-up and the Power Sneakers.

Hidden 1-Ups - There are five hidden 1-Ups in the game. The first one is in
Zone 1, Act 1. You play until you reach the first bed of spikes. After you
crosss the pit, the second tree has the prize. The second one is on the boss
level of Zone 1. Just fall on the second canyon and you will find the extra
guy. A third in Zone 2, Act 3 is straight to your left at the start. Then the
jungle has the fourth one in Zone 3, Act 3. Before you start to jump on the
green platform and make your way to the top, go to the right until you get
to the water. Jump in, go right, and get the 1-Up. The last one is hidden in
the water in Zone 4, Act 3. You encounter a spring that takes you up into a
long room hidden in the top left course. In that room will be rows of spikes.
Jump them safely and get the last 1-Up. 


SONIC THE HEDGEHOG 2
====================
Level Select - Go to the Title screen, then Options screen. Highlight the
sound select test box. With the pad, change the number of the sound test and
play them with the B button in this order: 19, 65, 9 and 17. When you play
song 17 you will hear a distintive ring sound at the beginning of the song.
Press START to exit back to the title screen. When the title screen appears,
hold A button and press START and you will see the level select screen.

Super Sonic - If you highlight the sound test box on the Options screen and
play the sounds in this order with the B button: 4, 1, 2 & 6. Choose any
level and when you collect 50 rings and you jump into the air, you become
Super Sonic. Press START then A to exit the level.

Debug Mode - If you highlight the sound test box on the Options screen and
play the sounds in this order with the B button: 1, 9, 9, 2, 1, 1, 2, 4
(Sonic Tuesday). Highlight stage, hold button A and press START to enter
level. While in a level, it is possible to change into an object.
Press B button to change objects and C buuton to duplicate objects.

2 Player Game on 1 Player Screen - Go to the options by pressing the pad
DOWN twice on the title screen. Make sure you are playing "Sonic and Tails".
Go into the game and using controller 2, move the pad in any direction, or
press any button and you will see that you can move Tails anywhere on the
screen separately from Sonic! This will make it easier to work as a team and
complete the game. Also since Tails can not die, you can use him to defeat
the bosses and just have Sonic avoid them. If you want to go back to the one
player mode, just leave Tails alone and he will go back to following Sonic.

Change into Super Sonic - You can change yourself into Super Sonic with the
following method. This is best accomplished with two players. Go into the
first level, collect 50 rings, and find the nearest Star Pole. Touch it and
jump up in the rotating stars to enter the bonus level. Use two players and
collect all the rings necessary to get the Chaos Emerald. Once you grab it,
press the Reset button on the Genesis.
When the title screen appears, go into the Options, and then press START to
get to the first level again. Repeat the exact same process over and over
and you will see that the bonus stages cahange, and you get different
emeralds each time. Once you collect all 7 Chaos Emeralds, go back into that
level. Now what you must do, is collect 50 rings and jump into the air. Wow!
You are now Super Sonic! He can jump faster and jump higher than before. His
rings go down every second, so stock up.


SPIDERMAN
=========
Short Cut to First Boss - Go to the option mode and select Nightmare
difficulty. Play the game and get into the first level warehouse. Go to the
right, past the first thug and the German Shepard. Next, jump on the first
crate and crawl to the right. You will go through the crate and right to the
Boss.

Money for Taking Pictures - To get the most money by taking pictures, snap
the following shots in these stages:
    Stage 1 - Forklift, Dr Octopus = $200
    Stage 2 - Alligator, Lizardman, go past Lizardman to snap Venom = $380
    Stage 3 - Lightening Creature, Electro = $300
    Stage 4 - Gorilla, Sandman, Venom =$400
    Stage 5 - J.J. Jameson, (then go directly above for a grey box on the
              top of the building), Brutal Biker, Hodgoblin, Venom = $440
    Stage 6 - Don't waste time.
     
Level Boss Strategies - 
Dr. Octopus: Get directly beneath him and punch. Try to trap him in the 
corner.
Lizard: Stay to one side of him. If he ducks, stand up briefly, duck and
keep firing.
Electro: Get on a ledge above him and keep shooting webs. You will be able 
to hit him and he won't be able to hit you.
Mr Sandman: Swing over to the left by the fire hydrant and spray him with
water. It takes only one hit.
Hobogoblin: Shoot up at him and hit him when he moves low.
Venom: Move to where you can see him. Activate your web shield and jump
over his shots. Hit him when you can, he's tough.
Kingpin: Activate your web shield and use jump kicks. Aim for his head.


SPLATTERHOUSE 2
===============
Level Select - At the title screen, go to the password select and put in these
codes to reach higher levels.

       Level 2 -  EDK  NAI  ZOL  LDL     Level 6 -  ADE  NAI  WRA  LKA
       Level 3 -  IDO  GEM  IAL  LDL     Level 7 -  EFH  XOE  IAL  LDL
       Level 4 -  ADE  XOE  ZOL  OME     Level 8 -  EDK  VEI  IAL  LDL
       Level 5 -  EFH  VEI  RAG  ORD


SPORTS TALK BASEBALL
====================
Quick Man Out - When you're out in the field and the other team gets a
single, keep throwing the ball around the bases. The runner on first will
attempt to steal second base and you will have an easy pick-off.


STEEL EMPIRE
============
Round Select - Go to the options screen and perform the sound test in the 
following order: sound 1 - twice, sound 9 - once, sound 2 - once. Once this
is done, a new category will be added to the options. Select Round from
1 to 7. Note: Worked on preliminary version of game.

Skip Levels - First plug in controller 2. Next, get past the title screen
and all of the options. Begin your game. Press the C button on controller 2
to skip ahead in your level, if it has a different section, and press it 
again to end without even fighting the Boss.

99 Ships - Enter the option mode from the title screen. While in the option
mode, set the difficulty to Hard, Ships at 2, Continues at 1, and then
choose sound 65 and press the A button. You will not hear any sound, but
when the game starts, you will begin your mission with 99 ships.

99 Bombs - Plug in your second controller. When you get to the ship selection
screen, push C, A, C, A, START and then B. You will hear a chime if the
trick worked. Once you start the game, you will have 99 bombs.


STREETS OF RAGE 2
=================
Extra Lives & Level of Difficulty - You will need a second controller in
Port #2. With the second controller, press START on the title screen. That
will take you to the Options screen. Move cursor with controller #2 down to
word OPTIONS. With buttons A and B held down, press START and it will give
you a new Options screen. This will let you select the number of lives and
the difficulty settings. 


STRIDER
=======
Dipodal Saucer Robots - Have the Dipodal Saucer robots through the whole game.
First get 2 robots (2 of your life bars will be read). Late in the first stage
you'll come to a container with the robot panther in it. Do not touch it!
Make sure you are shot once by the enemy, then go back and activate the
panther. The panther will leave and your original Dipodal Saucers will
appear. They will stay with you, even if you die. The only way to lose them
is by falling off the screen or using a continue.


SUPER MONACO G.P.
=================
Race in Last Race - To race in the last race of the second year, enter the
following code. If you crash, don't worry, you will still have enough points
to win the season.
                      0CUL 1BQ2 7900 0000
                      0611 110V 2D2B 5467
                      CA89 E6B1 8000 0003
                      0000 0000 F200 F66C


SYD OF VALIS
============
Unlimited Life and Yuko's Swimming Suit Bonus - On the title screen, press
the following buttons. UP, DOWN, LEFT, RIGHT, A, B, UP, DOWN and then START.
If you hear a signal sound, you have done the trick right. Once you start
the game now, Yuko will be in her swimming suit making her invincible and
impervious to attack damage. Yuko will also get bonus points for being in
this mode.

Music Test - Now you can hear all the cool tunes. At the title screen, press
and hold A, B, C and press START. After you do this you will see a music
selection screen. Just press A, B or C to change the tune.


TASK FORCE HARRIER EX
=====================
Debug Mode - Hold button A while turning on the power. When the title screen
appears, let go of A and push the following buttons: UP, DOWN, LEFT, RIGHT,
A, B, A, C, B. Now select "Config" on the title screen and you will see that
the option mode has changed. There are new optionscalled "Muteki" 
(invinciblity) and "Window" (changes the screen size). You can choose the
"Wide" screen option for a better view.
When in the level, press START and then A to skip levels.


TAZMANIA
========
Infinite Continues - The continue loop is in the Badlands. First go to the
Continue. It's high on a rock right before the bridge. To get the Continue,
let a rock monster follow you to the rock. Jump on the head, then jump on
the rock. Touch the milestone next. Then go back and get the 1-UP on the
rock's left edge. The loop is complete. Just keep repeating as many times as
you need.


TEAM USA BASKETBALL
===================
Play as Team USA in final game against the Netherlands - # XT7RB6
See Closing ceremonies - # WT7RDC

Play as Team USA in final game against Lithuania - # FNT7RBQ
See closing ceremonies - # FMT7RCO (Last entry is letter O)


TOEJAM AND EARL
===============
Hidden Level - It is possible to get to an island with pretty hula girl
inviting you in for a hot bath, and a lemonade stand to provide you with
extra life. To do it, get to the bottom, left of the islnd, activate either
Icarus Wings, or the Inner Tube to get over the water. Then go through
(or over) the water and you'll find the hidden island. Fall through the hole
in the center of the island and you'll be in the Hidden level.

Sneak up on Santa Claus - Wait until Santa is looking into his bag, and then
tip-toe up to him. If Santa looks up, freeze until he looks back into his 
bag. Then tip-toe towards him some more. If you reach him successfully, he'll
drop presents for you.


THUNDER FORCE 2
===============
Level Select - While turning on the Genesis, you will need to hold A, B, and
C. When the title screen appears, press START while holding these control
letters.


THUNDER FORCE 3
===============
Instant Weapons - Pause the game and press UP 10 times, B once, DOWN two
times, and B two more times. Unpause the game and you will have access to
all of the available weaponry.


TROUBLE SHOOTER
===============
Stage Select - Plug in controller 1, get to the title screen where it allows
you to choose to start or go to an option screen. On controller 2, press
START, RIGHT and C at the same time. You will see a stage select option come
up in between the title words. Press START, RIGHT and C again to advance
stage numbers. Timing is very critical.


TURRICAN
========
Customize Options - Go to the options screen and move the cursor to the
bottom of the screen. Hold the pad DOWN and press A, B, B, A, B, A, A, B, A,
A, B, A, A. An extra menu will let you modify weapons, lives, power and
stage select. If the option menu doesn't appear, press Up and repeat the 
button sequence again.


